";s:50:"http://wp4sae.org/discovering-the-truth-about-tips";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://wp4sae.org/discovering-the-truth-about-tips#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2016 23:45:41 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Sports & Athletics";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"http://wp4sae.org/discovering-the-truth-about-tips";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:394:"Snow Skiing Safety Tips for Beginners People who are out on a snow skiing adventure for the first time obviously have a lot to learn about this kind of environment. Yes, it&#8217;s such a fun place to enjoy, and you can do so many things to give yourself a lifetime of beautiful memories. However, just<a class="more-link" href="http://wp4sae.org/discovering-the-truth-about-tips">Read more</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"writer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2693:"<p>Snow Skiing Safety Tips for Beginners</p>\n<p> People who are out on a snow skiing adventure for the first time obviously have a lot to learn about this kind of environment. Yes, it&#8217;s such a fun place to enjoy, and you can do so many things to give yourself a lifetime of beautiful memories. However, just like any sport then and now, skiing has its own set of risks, especially if you do it in the wilderness. But of course, as long as you remain a responsible skier, you can always stay on the safe side of those slopes with a few precautions. .</p>\n<p> First of all, know that it&#8217;s important to get the right ski equipment. In fact, this is true for all sports that require equipment. Avoid borrowing from a friend, unless he is an expert skier who can tell if his gear is good for you. Renting may be a good option as long as you choose a pro shop, whether close to either your home or your destination. The most important thing to do prior to buying ski equipment as a newbie is to ask for advice from a pro. Again, it can be hazardous to wear the wrong equipment.</p>\n<p> Secondly, know and obey skiing rules. Rules are not made for no reason. They are meant to keep you safe, considering the condition of the landscape where you are about to ski. This is why you must never veer off the trails because there&#8217;s always a possibility of a drop off somewhere. Even more important if you&#8217;re skiing on an landscape you&#8217;ve never skied before. Best thing to do is to read different materials about the area so you can prepare better and be safer. Better yet, if you have the chance, talk to the locals. When you ski, always remember that those in front of you as well as below you have the right of way. </p>\n<p> You should also take note of skiing etiquette and codes of responsibility. Yes, it&#8217;s important to be nice and respectful to others. Also, you are responsible for being aware of the skiers around you. As mentioned, guidelines are provided for the safety of everyone on the slopes, specifically to avoid accidents and injuries. Skier codes of responsibility cover proper equipment care, which is important both for your safety and that of the others.</p>\n<p> At the end of the day, all you&#8217;d like to do on that mountain is enjoy time with friends and family. But of course, nothing can be fun or great enough if your safety is compromised. And you&#8217;re going to be just fine, provided your gear is right for you, and you have no problem observing all the skiing rules and codes and etiquette, which are all for your own good anyway.\n<p>Source: <a href="http://exoticskis.com/forum/default.aspx?g=posts&amp;m=575">street skiing</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"http://wp4sae.org/discovering-the-truth-about-tips/feed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"5 Takeaways That I Learned About Sports";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"http://wp4sae.org/5-takeaways-that-i-learned-about-sports";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://wp4sae.org/5-takeaways-that-i-learned-about-sports#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2016 07:27:45 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"